org.dgfoundation.amp.nireports.schema

Class NiCombinationContextTransactionMeasure

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.dgfoundation.amp.nireports.schema.NiReportedEntity<K>
      • org.dgfoundation.amp.nireports.schema.NiReportMeasure<CategAmountCell>
        • org.dgfoundation.amp.nireports.schema.NiCombinationContextTransactionMeasure

  • public class NiCombinationContextTransactionMeasure
extends NiReportMeasure<CategAmountCell>
    Measure defined as a linear combination of context measures (instances of NiCombinationContextTransactionMeasure).
    The measure is configured by being given a set of NiTransactionContextMeasure and corresponding numbers. The measure works by repeating the steps below for each and every cell in the Funding column:
    1. find a measure in the map for which NiTransactionContextMeasure.criterion returns nonnull
    2. if none exists, the given cell is ignored and no further processing happens
    3. if a match exists, the output of the criterion is multiplied by the value given at construction time and the resulting cell goes in the output
    4. if multiple matches exist, the behaviour is undefined. In the current implementation, an arbitrary match will be used for the previous step
